  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail and finely dice (no need to peel!) your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lancashire-style-lamb-hotpot-with-buttery-peas/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into thin discs</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 2-3 min or until just cooked (this is known as 'parboiling')</p><p>Once done, drain the<strong> sliced potatoes</strong> and leave them to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lancashire-style-lamb-hotpot-with-buttery-peas/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>lamb mince </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go, then once the lamb has started to brown, drain the excess oil from the pan and discard</p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>to the pan, give everything a good mix up and cook for 30 secs and reboil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lancashire-style-lamb-hotpot-with-buttery-peas/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> diced onion</strong> and <strong>carrot</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Once slightly softened, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> onion marmalade</strong>, <strong>marmite</strong>, <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your<strong> dried thyme </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 1 min further</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lancashire-style-lamb-hotpot-with-buttery-peas/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>beef stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened to a gravy-like consistency and the lamb is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>lamb filling</strong></p><p>Transfer the <strong>lamb filling</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lancashire-style-lamb-hotpot-with-buttery-peas/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Layer the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>sliced potatoes</strong> on top</p><p>Divide a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> into little pieces and scatter over the top with<strong> </strong>the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>dried thyme</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven and cook for 25-30 min or until the potatoes are brown and crispy – this is your <strong>Lancashire-style lamb hotpot</strong></p><p>Once done, remove it from the oven and set aside to cool a little (this helps the flavours to develop and makes it easier to serve!)</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lancashire-style-lamb-hotpot-with-buttery-peas/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>When the hotpot is nearly ready, add your<strong> blanched peas</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over them to refresh them</p><p>Drain the peas, add a small knob of<strong> butter</strong> and mix it all together – these are your <strong>buttery peas</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lancashire-style-lamb-hotpot-with-buttery-peas/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Lancashire-style lamb hotpot </strong>with the <strong>buttery peas </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
